# 1. ドキドキ、バレンタイン！

Ichika: (School's finally out... This day felt so long for some reason.)
Ichika: (Is it because I'm just that excited about having singing practice with Kusanagi?)
Student A: Valentine's Day is coming up! I can't wait to share chocolates with everyone♪
Ichika: (Valentine's Day... It's already that time of year.)
Ichika: (I'd like to give something to Miku and the others... But what would be best?)
Ichika: (Oh, actually, I think the mall's having a Valentine's Day fair. That might be a good place to look.)
Student A: What are you gonna make? I wanna try my hand at baking a chocolate tart.
Student B: You are...? I was thinking about being lazy and just buying some...
Student A: What?! Why?! If we're gonna exchange them, they should all be homemade!
Student B: They don't absolutely have to be homemade. I mean, store-bought ones just look better and more appetizing, you know?
Student A: Y-Yeah, I get what you mean... But homemade means that there's just that much more love baked into them, right?
Ichika: ...!
Ichika: (More love baked into them...)
Ichika: (I agree that a homemade gift would do a better job of showing someone just how much you appreciate them as opposed to a store-bought one...)
Ichika: (But what would I make...? I don't really know how to bake sweets or anything...)
Ichika: (No, now's not the time for this. I need to hurry. I shouldn't keep Kusanagi waiting!)
Ichika: ♪————!
Ichika: Okay... H-How was that...?
Nene: Really good. I thought you also did well at Shibuya Festa, but you seem to just keep getting better and better.
Nene: You already had such a clear, refined voice, but it's like it's become even more refined...
Nene: I'm guessing that you feel a lot more confident about your singing now.
Nene: Oh... S-Sorry, I didn't mean to sound uppity...
Ichika: No, it's okay. Actually, that made me really happy!
Ichika: I mean, it's hard for me to tell how my singing is changing...
Ichika: And it means a lot coming from you, Kusanagi. I feel like I've grown quite a bit now, so thank you.
Nene: O-Okay...
Nene: At the same time, I should also be thanking you... I've learned so much by practicing with you, Hoshino.
Ichika: Wait, you have...?
Nene: Yeah. Whenever I practice with you, I notice things that I don't normally...
Nene: It's so nice to be able to practice singing with someone else outside of the Wonder Stage like this.
Ichika: Really...? Then, I'm glad.
Nene: Anyway... Wanna try singing together next?
Ichika: Yes! Oh, but... I'd like to get something to drink first. All this singing has made me parched.
Nene: Oh, I think I'd like something as well. There's a convenience store just right there, so let's head over together.
Convenience Store Clerk: Thank you, have a nice day.
Nene: I'm glad that we were able to get some drinks, but...
Ichika: That store... It was covered with Valentine's Day merchandise.
Nene: There were so many different chocolates on display in front of the register too. I guess it really is just around the corner.
Ichika: That reminds me of some girls who I overheard talking about Valentine's today.
Ichika: When I heard them talking, I began thinking about what I'm going to do, but couldn't really come to a decision.
Nene: Oh, are you planning on giving some gifts to people?
Ichika: Yes, my bandmates. But I don't really know how to bake sweets or anything, so I initially thought about just buying something from the store...
Ichika: But one of those girls said how it'd be more meaningful if you made a gift yourself... So, I sort of want to do that instead.
Nene: I see... I think I'm in the same boat as you.
Ichika: Wait, Kusanagi, you too?
Nene: Yeah. I also initially thought that something store-bought would be fine... However, after rehearsal yesterday, we started talking about Valentine's Day...
Emu: Isn't Valentine's Day such a wonderhoy event?!
Emu: I'm gonna make some really amazing sweets, so stay tuned, everyone! I don't know what yet... But it's gonna be really awesome!
Nene: After Emu said that, I started thinking that I should also make something.
Ichika: Hehe. That sounds like something Otori would say.
Nene: Unfortunately, I also don't really know how to bake and stuff, so I'm not sure what to do.
Ichika: Isn't there a good solution out there...?
Nene: Oh... What if we made something other than sweets?
Ichika: Something other than sweets?
Nene: Yeah. Handmade accessories or trinkets... Food's not the only way to show someone that you appreciate them.
Ichika: True... That never came to mind for me...
Ichika: Also, not being limited to sweets means we might have more options available to us.
Nene: Yeah, I agree.
Ichika: Oh, then... What if we tried making our gifts together, Kusanagi...?
Nene: Huh? Together...?
Ichika: Yes. I mean, it could be fun to make our gifts through some trial and error.
Ichika: Oh, of course... You don't have to if you don't want to, Kusanagi.
Nene: Oh... N-No, that does sound fun. I... I'd like to try making something with you, Hoshino.
Ichika: I'm glad to hear that...
Nene: But what could we make? The only things that immediately come to mind are hair accessories and stuff...
Ichika: That's an option. However, Saki and Honami may like that, but Shiho might not...
Nene: Right... We should go for something that everyone's gonna like, but that we can manage to make...
Ichika: Yeah...
Ichika: Still can't think of anything...
Ichika: Honami probably would've already come up with something too.
Nene: Wait, really?
Ichika: Oh, um... Yeah... She's really good at knitting and making accessories by hand.
Nene: Wow, I didn't know that... Then, she probably would know what to do in this sort of situation.
Ichika: Yeah, I might just ask her for some advice now...
Nene: Huh? I thought you were gonna make something for her.
Ichika: I am. However, as much as I want it to be a surprise, I'd rather give a gift that's as nice as it can be...
Nene: I see... Sorry, I wish I could've come up with something...
Ichika: No, Kusanagi, it's okay. You don't need to apologize. Anyway, I'll try sending her a message now...
Ichika: Umm... <Sorry, I know this is sudden, but there's something I need to ask you. Kusanagi and I were trying to come up with something we can make for Valentine's Day...>
Ichika: <Do you know anything that's simple and beginner friendly...?>
Ichika: It's kind of straight to the point, but I hope she understands...
Ichika: Oh, she's already replied.
Honami: <How about scented candles? They're actually pretty easy to make and hard to mess up.>
Ichika: Scented candles...? As in the ones that give off really nice aromas? You can make those yourself...?
Nene: Yeah, that could be really good since anyone we give them to can get use out of them...
Ichika: You saved us, Honami. It's amazing how she can come up with an idea like this on the spot... Wait, huh...?! She keeps sending more...!
Nene: Oh... Resin jewelry, leather goods... Wow, there's so many.
Ichika: Still, by comparison, I feel like scented candles are going to be the easiest to make and decorate.
Ichika: Shiho would also probably like that the most, so I'd like to try making some...
Nene: Yeah, I agree... Let's go with that.
Ichika: Then, I'll send Honami a reply... <Thanks. I think we'll go with the scented candles that you first suggested.>
Ichika: Hm...? She replied back...?
Honami: <I think I can teach you how to make them, so how about we all do it together?>
Ichika: Wait... Honami's going to teach us...?!
Nene: What...?
Nene: H-Hang on... Hoshino, that makes sense since you're her friend, but me...?
Ichika: She's already invited you, so you should be more than welcome to join us. To put you at ease, I can ask just to be sure.
Nene: O-Okay...
Nene: (I-I'm kinda nervous... I haven't really had a chance to talk to Mochizuki before...)
Nene: (But I want to get to know her better. I don't want to let this opportunity go to waste...)
Nene: Then, I'd like to join you two...
Ichika: Great. I'll let Honami know right now.
Nene: *Nod*
Ichika: (I wasn't sure what we should make, but I'm glad I asked her for some advice...)
Ichika: (And Honami said she'd teach us... I need to do my best with Kusanagi to make sure our scented candles turn out well!)
